<section class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-text">
        <h2>Hey, I'm Courtney Fradreck</h2>
        <p>
            I'm a Zimbabwe-based software engineering student, startup builder, and tech community lead who treats
            CourtNotes as my public notebook. This space captures the messy-but-fun journey of learning in public,
            from experiments in Eleventy to reflections on leadership.
        </p>
        <p>
            By day I'm the CEO and project lead at Proxyon Technologies where we're building AgriLease - a mobile-first
            marketplace that helps farmers discover, book, and pay for agricultural equipment with trustworthy local
            logistics and flexible payments. This page is where I connect the dots between that work and the person behind it.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-hero-img">
        <img src="https://courtney-taga.web.app/assets/images/courtney.jpg" alt="Photo of Courtney Fradreck">
    </div>
</section>

<section class="about-content">
    <div class="about-section">
        <h2>What is CourtNotes?</h2>
        <p>
            CourtNotes is the running commentary of my career - raw notes, honest rants, and practical lessons from
            product design, hackathons, and community leadership. Each post keeps me accountable to building in public
            and opens the door for future collaborators.
        </p>
        <p>
            Expect dispatches on software craft, startup execution, and why Africa-focused products need context-aware
            tooling. If you see an experiment here, it probably shipped in a sprint elsewhere.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
        <h2>Lead, Build, Share</h2>
        <p>
            I lead the Proxyon team on AgriLease while also serving as the Tech Lead for GDG on Campus at my university.
            Coaching peers, running workshops, and refining pitches are as core to my routine as pull requests.
        </p>
        <p>
            Recent projects span React Native (TypeScript), React + Vite, Tailwind CSS, Firebase, and Eleventy. Clean UI,
            scalable architecture, and functionality-first decisions keep every build shippable.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-gallery">
        <img src="https://placehold.co/600x400/f2f2f7/1c1c1e?text=Coding+Setup" alt="Desk setup with laptop and notebook">
        <img src="https://placehold.co/600x400/f2f2f7/1c1c1e?text=Work+in+Progress" alt="Whiteboard sketches for AgriLease flows">
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
        <h2>Beyond the Keyboard</h2>
        <p>
            Long-term, I'm chasing a Forbes Africa 30 Under 30 slot while staying grounded in useful tech. When I'm not
            prototyping, you'll catch me refining product decks or looping Kendrick Lamar, J. Cole, Sjava, Nasty C, and A-Reece.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-apple-music" data-source="apple-music">
        <h2>On Apple Music</h2>

        <div class="apple-music-playlist">
            <div class="apple-music-playlist-head">
                <h3>Recently Played</h3>
                <p>The last few tracks I've had on.</p>
            </div>
            {% if music.recent.length %}
            <ol class="apple-music-tracklist">
                {% for track in music.recent %}
                <li>
                    <a class="apple-music-track" href="{{ track.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        <img src="{{ track.artwork }}" width="56" height="56" loading="lazy" alt="Album artwork for {{ track.name }}">
                        <span class="apple-music-track-info">
                            <span class="apple-music-track-name">{{ track.name }}</span>
                            <span class="apple-music-track-artist">{{ track.artist }}</span>
                        </span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                {% endfor %}
            </ol>
            {% else %}
            <p class="apple-music-note">
                Nothing to show right now — recently played tracks appear here once the Apple Music token is configured and the next build runs.
            </p>
            {% endif %}
        </div>

        {% if music.heavyRotation %}
        <div class="apple-music-playlist">
            <div class="apple-music-playlist-head">
                {% if music.heavyRotation.artwork %}
                <img class="apple-music-playlist-cover" src="{{ music.heavyRotation.artwork }}" width="64" height="64" loading="lazy" alt="{{ music.heavyRotation.name }} playlist cover">
                {% endif %}
                <div>
                    <h3>{{ music.heavyRotation.name }}</h3>
                    <p>
                        My on-repeat playlist, auto-built by Apple Music.
                        {% if music.heavyRotation.url %}<a href="{{ music.heavyRotation.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open in Apple Music →</a>{% endif %}
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <ol class="apple-music-tracklist">
                {% for track in music.heavyRotation.tracks %}
                <li>
                    <a class="apple-music-track" href="{{ track.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        <img src="{{ track.artwork }}" width="56" height="56" loading="lazy" alt="Album artwork for {{ track.name }}">
                        <span class="apple-music-track-info">
                            <span class="apple-music-track-name">{{ track.name }}</span>
                            <span class="apple-music-track-artist">{{ track.artist }}</span>
                        </span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                {% endfor %}
            </ol>
        </div>
        {% endif %}
    </div>

    <div class="about-cta">
        <img src="https://courtnotes.netlify.app/assets/blog-images/img-20250125-wa0038~2-1-.jpg" alt="Call to connect banner">
        <h2>Come Along for the Ride</h2>
        <p>
            If you're into real talk about startups, engineering, and community building, you're in the right place. Dive
            into the blog and say hi - I answer every thoughtful DM.
        </p>
        <button onclick="window.location.href='/blog/'">Check Out the Blog</button>
    </div>
</section>


